,"1086–1135":"1086–1135","0982–1059":"0982–1059","1080":"1080","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1054":"1054","1086":"1086","1064":"1064","1030":"1030","1059":"1059","1048":"1048","0982":"0982","1135":"1135","1046":"1046","1045":"1045","about 1046":"about 1046","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, England","Normandel, Orne, Basse-Normandie, France":"Normandel, Orne, Lower Normandy, France","Dutton or Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Dutton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Cheshire, Lancashire, and Staffordshire): habitational name from either Dutton in Cheshire or Dutton in Lancashire. The first is named from Old English <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’; the second from the Old English personal name <i>Dudd(a)</i> (see   Dodd   1) + Old English <i>tūn</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Dodd","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Dodd(e)</i>, <i>Dudd(e)</i>, Old English <i>Dodd(a)</i>, <i>Dudd(a)</i>, a name of uncertain origin which remained in fairly widespread and frequent use from Lincolnshire to Devon and from Essex to Lancashire in England until the 14th century.","English: nickname from Middle English <i>dod</i>, a word of uncertain meaning, possibly a ‘lumpish, thickset person’ (compare modern English dialect <i>dod</i> ‘bunch or heap’), or by extension a ‘foolish person’ (compare Middle English <i>dode-mused</i> ‘stupid’), or perhaps a derivative of <i>dodden</i> ‘to shave (the head), to trim (hair)’, hence ‘the hairless or close-cropped one’.","English: possibly a modern variant of <b>Daud</b> or <b>Dowd</b>, the former arising from the Middle English personal name <i>Daud(e)</i>, an extended form of   Daw  , and the latter from the Middle English personal name <i>Doude</i>, perhaps a side-form of either <i>Dodde</i> or of <i>Daude</i>, a pet form of   Ralph  ."]}]},{"name":"Odard","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Same as the Alemannic name Gothart; from cuat-hart, very good."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Odard Dutton 1st Lord Dutton was born about 1046, in Normandel, Orne, Lower Normandy, France as the son of Father of Odard de Dutton, ist Lord of Dutton. He had at least 1 son with Lady Alice Frome. He died in Dutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1046–":"umbes 1046–Surnud","1030–1080":"1030–1080","1045–1080":"1045–1080","1046–Male":"1046–Surnud","1048–Male":"1048–Surnud","1054–Male":"1054–Surnud","1055–Male":"1055–Surnud","1064–Female":"1064–Surnud","1086–1135":"1086–1135","0982–1059":"0982–1059","1080":"1080","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1054":"1054","1086":"1086","1064":"1064","1030":"1030","1059":"1059","1048":"1048","0982":"0982","1135":"1135","1046":"1046","1045":"1045","about 1046":"umbes 1046","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, England","Normandel, Orne, Basse-Normandie, France":"Normandel, Orne, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Dutton or Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1046–":"noin 1046–Kuollut","1030–1080":"1030–1080","1045–1080":"1045–1080","1046–Male":"1046–Kuollut","1048–Male":"1048–Kuollut","1054–Male":"1054–Kuollut","1055–Male":"1055–Kuollut","1064–Female":"1064–Kuollut","1086–1135":"1086–1135","0982–1059":"0982–1059","1080":"1080","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1054":"1054","1086":"1086","1064":"1064","1030":"1030","1059":"1059","1048":"1048","0982":"0982","1135":"1135","1046":"1046","1045":"1045","about 1046":"noin 1046","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, England","Normandel, Orne, Basse-Normandie, France":"Normandel, Orne, Basse-Normandie, Ranska","Dutton or Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1046–":"environ 1046–Décédé","1030–1080":"1030–1080","1045–1080":"1045–1080","1046–Male":"1046–Décédé","1048–Male":"1048–Décédé","1054–Male":"1054–Décédé","1055–Male":